# Logging

**Backend:** use the shared Pino-based logger (see existing backend modules). **Frontend:** use `logEvent` and `logError` from `@/app/_common/_lib/logger` — **not** `console.log` or `console.error` in app code (Storybook/tests may use console where practical).

- `event`: dot-separated name. Backend: `domain.action` (e.g. request-scoped). Frontend client observability: `ui.*` (e.g. `ui.error_boundary.caught`, `ui.next_error_boundary.editor`).
- Include `requestId` and `userId` when relevant; pass extra detail in `context.metadata`.
- Structured `metadata`, not string interpolation.
- No secrets, tokens, full PDFs, or huge prompts (logger redacts common fields).
